---
import Header from '~/components/Header.astro';
let title = 'Astro WordPress demo';
import '~/styles/global.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <div class="flex flex-col p-10">
      <div class="mb-5 text-4xl font-bold">Welcome to AstroPress</div>
      <article class="prose lg:prose-xl">
        <p>AstroPress is a combination of the amazing Static Site Generator Astro and Headless WordPress as the CMS.</p>
        <p>
          Have a play around by navigating the menu above, this menu is generated by WordPress and the pages are
          WordPress content.
        </p>
        <strong>Todo:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>☑️ Blog pages</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>More information</strong>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="">Find this project on GitHub</a></li>
          <li><a href="">Read the complete article</a></li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
